Digitaria decumbens

   [922.jpg]
    Authority   Stent.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms   Digitaria eriantha ssp. pentzii, Digitaria pentzii Stent.
   Common names pangola grass, wooly finger grass
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 922

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A densely tufted grass with simple or branched culms
   up to 120 cm high, strongly stoloniferous with numerous runners at all
   the nodes and rooting from most of them. USES Used for hay and pasture
   and withstands very heavy grazing. Also useful for erosion control, but
   has to be established vegetatively. KILLING T It becomes frosted and
   brown when exposed to cold but retains its nutritive value. GROWING
   PERIOD Summer-growing perennial grass. It flowers in 79-96 days at 14
   hours and 138-151 hours at 11 hours daylight. COMMON NAMES Woolly
   finger grass. FURTHER INF Scientific synonym: D. eriantha var
   stolonifera. In Zimbabwe it is found at elevations from 450 to 1100 m
   and is common in dry-land areas on fertile clay. It tolerate drought
   well. Dry matter yields are usually between 27-31 t/ha.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index - In Ecocrop as synonym Digitaria decumbens
   [11]Grassland Index
   Skerman P 1990 pp 363-365 [DRA FER, TEXT, KTMP, RAIN, PHO]
   Bogdan A 1977 pp 124-125 [USE]

